<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-34-0308 </DOCNO><TEXT>Radiation trapping currently creates one of the major limitations on populationinversion, gain, and size in x-ray lasers. The resulting increase inlower-level population may be reduced by photodepletion to higher energylevels. A natural energy match between hydrogenic lasing ions of nuclearcharge Z, for n = 2 to 4 or 6 excitation, and Z/2 radiating ions providesa scalable system for even-Z elements.</TEXT></DOC>